{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.8",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 8,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 8 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:1",
      "text": "Does not wisdom call, Does not understanding raise her voice?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:2",
      "text": "On the heights beside the way, in the paths she takes her stand;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:3",
      "text": "beside the gates in front of the town, at the entrance of the portals she cries aloud:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:4",
      "text": "“To you, O men, I call, and my cry is to the sons of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:5",
      "text": "O simple ones, learn prudence; O foolish men, pay attention.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:6",
      "text": "Hear, for I will speak noble things, and from my lips will come what is right;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:7",
      "text": "for my mouth will utter truth; wickedness is an abomination to my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:8",
      "text": "All the words of my mouth are righteous; there is nothing twisted or crooked in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:9",
      "text": "They are all straight to him who understands and right to those who find knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:10",
      "text": "Take my instruction instead of silver, and knowledge rather than choice gold;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:11",
      "text": "for wisdom is better than jewels, and all that you may desire cannot compare with her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:12",
      "text": "I, wisdom, dwell in prudence, and I find knowledge and discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:13",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is hatred of evil. Pride and arrogance and the way of evil and perverted speech I hate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:14",
      "text": "I have counsel and sound wisdom, I have insight, I have strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:15",
      "text": "By me kings reign, and rulers decree what is just;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:16",
      "text": "by me princes rule, and nobles govern the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:17",
      "text": "I love those who love me, and those who seek me diligently find me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:18",
      "text": "Riches and honor are with me, enduring wealth and prosperity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:19",
      "text": "My fruit is better than gold, even fine gold, and my yield than choice silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:20",
      "text": "I walk in the way of righteousness, in the paths of justice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:21",
      "text": "endowing with wealth those who love me, and filling their treasuries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:22",
      "text": "The Lord created me at the beginning of his work, the first of his acts of old.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:23",
      "text": "Ages ago I was set up, at the first, before the beginning of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:24",
      "text": "When there were no depths I was brought forth, when there were no springs abounding with water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:25",
      "text": "Before the mountains had been shaped, before the hills, I was brought forth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:26",
      "text": "before he had made the earth with its fields, or the first of the dust of the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:27",
      "text": "When he established the heavens, I was there, when he drew a circle on the face of the deep,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:28",
      "text": "when he made firm the skies above, when he established the fountains of the deep,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:29",
      "text": "when he assigned to the sea its limit, so that the waters might not transgress his command, when he marked out the foundations of the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:30",
      "text": "then I was beside him, like a master workman; and I was daily his delight, rejoicing before him always,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:31",
      "text": "rejoicing in his inhabited world and delighting in the sons of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:32",
      "text": "And now, my sons, listen to me: happy are those who keep my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:33",
      "text": "Hear instruction and be wise, and do not neglect it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:34",
      "text": "Happy is the man who listens to me, watching daily at my gates, waiting beside my doors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:35",
      "text": "For he who finds me finds life and obtains favor from the Lord;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.8.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 8:36",
      "text": "but he who misses me injures himself; all who hate me love death.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
